Forgot Root Password "Give root password for maintenance"

To reset your root password:

1. When the GRUB loader shows during boot press the spare bar to pause boot.

2. Select "Advanced options for ubuntu"

3. Type 'e' to edit the commands before booting.

4. At the end on the line that starts with 'linux' replace RO to RW (change mode from Read Only to Read and Write).

5. Add 'init=/bin/bash' to the end of the 'linux' line .

6. Press Ctrl-X or F10 to boot.

8. Change your root password:

# passwd root

10. Reboot your server using CTR-ALT-DELETE.

11. You will now be able to login with your new root password.
